.TH "gserial_disconnect" 9 "gserial_disconnect" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gserial_disconnect \- notify TTY I/O glue that USB link is inactive
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" gserial_disconnect
.BI "(struct gserial *gser "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "gser" 12
the function, on which \fBgserial_connect\fP was called
.SH "CONTEXT"
any (usually from irq)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is called to deactivate endpoints and let the TTY layer know
that the connection went inactive ... not unlike "hangup".

On return, the state is as if \fBgserial_connect\fP had never been called;
there is no active USB I/O on these endpoints.
